.help nxdisplay December2011 gemini.gnirs
.ih
NAME
.nf
nxdisplay -- Quick display of cross-dispersed data
.fi
.ih
USAGE
nxdisplay image frame
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls image
The MEF image to display.  This should contain GNIRS cross-dispersed data,
cut (using NSCUT, probably via NSREDUCE) so that different orders are in
different extensions.
.le
.ls frame = 1
The destination frame in the image display.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION

This task displays all the science extensions for GNIRS cross-dispersed
data to a single frame in the image display.
.ih
EXAMPLE

.nf
  cl> nxdisplay image
.fi
.ih
BUGS AND LIMITATIONS
The task forces stdimage to imt2048.
.ih
SEE ALSO
nscut, nsreduce
.endhelp
